avior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on generated narrative quality/faithfulness, which is model-output dependent and can vary. A deterministic stub would hide factuality and omission errors. Rejected Workflow because this behavior targets one generation decision, not multiple agentic stages chained together.","test_description":"Run summary generation against a fixed set of representative inputs using the real model, score outputs with factuality checks (key-value inclusion, no contradictions/hallucinations), and require pass thresholds over repeated trials.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"This explicitly requires an externally visible side effect verified by round-trip observation (email arrives in real inbox), which triggers System. Rejected Agentic because the stated acceptance is inbox delivery correctness; it does not require evaluating model output quality.","test_description":"Run the scheduled job end-to-end against reachable source services and a real email delivery path, then verify in recipient mailbox via real readback that exactly one report email arrived with expected subject/body sections and attachments/format.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","required_reality_check_level":"System",